@startuml
title Chat Flow: Input -> Backend -> cardRouter -> Entities -> Features

actor User
participant ChatInput as CI
participant ChatStream as CS
participant "Backend" as BE
participant ChatMessagesContext as Ctx
participant cardRouter as Router
participant "Entities.*Card" as Card
participant "Features.*Form" as Form
participant "lib/api/generated" as API
participant "app/providers/query" as RQ

User -> CI: type message + submit
CI -> CS: onSubmit(text)
CS -> BE: POST /chat (text, session, context)
BE --> CS: stream messages + card-hint\n{ type: "ChartCard", props: {...} }

CS -> Ctx: dispatch(addMessage, addCardHint)
Ctx -> Router: resolve(card-hint)
Router -> Card: render(CardComponent, props)

' Card may be a read-only entity view or actionable widget
Card -> API: (optional) GET data for view
API -> RQ: useQuery(fetcher)
RQ --> Card: cached/fetched data

' Card can expose callbacks that lead to mutations
User -> Card: click "Edit" / "Create" / "Link"
Card -> Form: open() with initial values
User -> Form: submit payload
Form -> API: POST/PUT/PATCH/DELETE
API -> RQ: useMutation(fetcher)
RQ --> Form: success (invalidate queries)

Form -> Ctx: notify(updated/deleted)
Ctx -> Card: refresh via query invalidation
Card -> Ctx: push follow-up message (optional)

@enduml
